Feature: (Imperturbable Charm)

    Makes objects such as doors impenetrable (by everything, including sounds
    and objects).

    Pronunciation: - 
    Seen/mentioned:
        The spell is used by Mrs Weasley in Order of the Phoenix on the door of
        the room in which an Order meeting was being held, to prevent her sons,
        Fred and George, from eavesdropping (using their extendable ears). Also
        mentioned in Half-Blood Prince when Harry, Ron, and Hermione followed
        Draco to Borgin and Burkes and used extendable ears
